decreases along the stator and the speed thus increases. In short, the stator acts

19
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:47,520
like a nozzle. As the speed of the jet increases in the stator, kinetic energy

20
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:51,920
increases. As there is no net energy transfer in the fluid in stator section,

21
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:55,800
the pressure and temperature of the jet should decrease to keep the total energy

22
00:01:55,800 --> 00:02:03,280
constant. Now, the next row of rotors is added. The stator also makes sure that the

23
