25
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:21,120
steam turbine. There is an important term while designing steam turbines, namely

26
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:25,440
degree of reaction. This term is calculated by dividing pressure and

27
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:29,920
temperature energy by the total energy change in the rotor. Pressure and

28
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:34,760
temperature energy together is called enthalpy. The degree of reaction decides

29
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:40,840
what type of steam turbine it is. As the pressure of the steam undergoes a

30
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:44,880
drastic reduction during steam turbine operation, its volume increases

31
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:49,360
proportionally. To accommodate such an expanded steam, we have to increase the

32
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:56,560
flow area. Otherwise, the flow speed will become too high. This is the reason why

33
00:02:56,560 --> 00:03:01,520
the steam turbine blades are too long towards the outlet. You can see how long

34
