the last stage turbine blades are compared to the first stage blades. The tips

35
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:10,600
of such long blades will have very high velocity compared to the root. A twist is

36
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:14,080
given to it so that all blade cross sections will remain at an optimum

37
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:22,880
angle of attack. This kind of large turbine uses two such symmetrical units. You

38
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:32,480
can see how the steam is equally divided between these units. High capacity

39
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:36,400
power plants use different stages of steam turbines, such as high pressure

40
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:44,640
turbine, intermediate pressure turbine, and low pressure turbines. All these

41
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:51,360
units are attached to a single rotating shaft. The shaft in turn is connected to

42
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:57,560
a generator. The reason for such different stages is quite interesting. With

43
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:02,160
greater steam temperature comes greater power plant efficiency. This is

44
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:07,960
according to the second law of thermodynamics. But we cannot have

45
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:12,160
temperature greater than 600 degrees Celsius since the turbine blade material

46
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:18,400
will not withstand temperature more than that. Temperature of the steam decreases

47
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:23,440
as it flows along the rows of the blade. Consequently, a great way to increase

48
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:29,080
power plant efficiency is to add more heat after the first stage. So after the

49
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:36,280
first stage, the steam is bypassed to the boiler and more heat is added. This is

50
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:41,080
known as reheating. This will increase the steam temperature again, leading to

51
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:48,480
higher power plant efficiency and output. One challenging problem in power plant

52
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:52,920
operation is to keep the speed of the steam turbine constant. This is important

53
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:56,480
since frequency of the electricity produced is directly proportional to the

54
00:04:56,480 --> 00:05:01,160
generator speed. However, depending on the load or power demand, the steam turbine

55
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:07,160
speed will vary. To keep the steam turbine speed constant, a steam flow governing

56
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:13,460
mechanism is used. If the steam turbine rotates at a higher speed, the control

57
00:05:13,460 --> 00:05:17,400
valve will automatically reduce the steam flow rate to the turbine until the

58
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:21,920
speed becomes normal. If the turbine rotates at a low speed, the inverse will

59
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:27,200
be done. In this way, the balance of power demand and power supply will be

